<section class="process">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-label">How It Works</div>
    <h2 class="section-headline">Three steps. Zero friction.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="process-steps">
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step-num">01</div>
      <div class="process-step-content">
        <h3>Homeowner enters address</h3>
        <p>A potential customer visits your Scopilot page, enters their address, and immediately sees aerial and street-level imagery of their property. No app to download. No account to create.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step-num">02</div>
      <div class="process-step-content">
        <h3>They draw and describe the project</h3>
        <p>Using the interactive map, they outline the project area — driveway, pour pad, excavation zone. They answer guided questions: tear-out required? Drainage concerns? Access point? They upload photos of the site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="process-step">
      <div class="process-step-num">03</div>
      <div class="process-step-content">
        <h3>You receive a qualified lead</h3>
        <p>Scopilot delivers a complete project brief: address, approximate measurements, uploaded photos, customer responses, and a ballpark estimate range. You decide whether to pursue it — no wasted drives, no guesswork.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>